CSS CHEAT SHEET

Reference:
*https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp
*https://css-tricks.com/almanac/

Cascading Style Sheets at the most basic level it
indicates that the order of CSS rules matter.

.class
#id
*
element
element, element /* este es usado para poner las mismas propiedades a dos diferentes etiquetas*/
element element /*este se usa para aquellos que tengan combinados sus dos elementos por ejemplo <h2> home <p>gnome</p> </h2>*/
element > element
element + element
:hover
:last-child
:first-child
!importan (not recommended)


What selectors win out in the cascade depends on:
-Specifity
-Importance
-Sourse Order
